            {{#marginal}}




A {{widget}} is sold for \${{price}} per item. Suppose that the number of items produced is equal to the number of items sold and that
the cost (in dollars) of producing x {{widget}}s is given by the
following function:
C(x)={{cost_function}}.




Explain and demonstrate how to find the marginal revenue, the marginal cost, and the marginal profit
in this situation.


            {{/marginal}}

answer.ol:
            {{#tangent}}




The equation of the tangent line is y = {{tanline}}.


            {{/tangent}}
            {{#motion}}        
                {{#elapsed}}







Position: {{position}} {{units}}







Velocity: {{velocity}} {{units}} per second







Acceleration: {{acceleration}} {{units}} per s^2




                {{/elapsed}}
            {{/motion}}
            {{#marginal}}




The marginal cost is {{marginal_cost}},
the marginal revenue is {{price}},
and the marginal profit is {{marginal_profit}}.


            {{/marginal}}
